Key Match Events: Jon Dagur Thorsteinsson scored Iceland's winner early in the match.
John Stones took a heavy challenge at the outset and made way at half-time with his right foot heavily strapped.
Harry Kane missed a big chance in the 28th minute, blazing a volley off target.
Marc Guéhi made an important block on a shot from Arnor Ingvi Traustason before the end of the first half.
Phil Foden dragged a shot wide after a Gordon pull-back in the second half.
Palmer tried and failed to round Valdimarsson following a Rice pass.
Sverrir Ingason escaped Guéhi on a corner but headed too close to Ramsdale.
Post-Match Reflections: Gareth Southgate had to urge his players to stay calm during the first half.
Southgate's team flattered to deceive in creative terms, with lots of flicks but not enough power and conviction.
The post-match lap of appreciation was flat, reflecting the performance.
